<!--
    Luxembourgish (Lëtzebuergesch) — lb
    Script : Latin (+ ë é); LTR.
    Approx.: ~400 000 L1 speakers (Luxembourg).
    Register: Standard Luxembourgish (Standardlëtzebuergesch) following the
              official orthography (Spellechecker / lod.lu norms, 2024 edition).
    Notes  : Luxembourgish is the national language of Luxembourg, alongside
             French and German as administrative languages.  It is used in
             everyday speech and increasingly in official writing since the
             2021 language legislation.  Key orthographic rules: ë is used in
             many unstressed syllables; é in loanwords from French; the letter
             combination "äi" is common.  "Binge drinking" → iwwerméisseg
             Drénken / Saufen — the neutral register term iwwerméisseg Drénken
             is preferred.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
